      "writtenOn": "2018-06-06T19:49:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why is only float3 packed? As written, this means that float3 has a smaller alignment than float2, which would be very surprising. Why do we believe that that is the case?\n\nWhy is it only packed when fieldOffset is specified?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 735,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 740,
        "endChar": 9
      },
      "revId": "9034332a4575c5309954c9e079c12a8c337ad10d",
